						{
							"id": "ses_2d65d8859ffeeIEuoz9TRZpzv8",
							"title": "Agentic AI context management: planning and style considerations",
							"updatedAt": 1774520011019,
							"messageCount": 0,
							"processing": true
						}
					],
					"roots": false
				},
				{
					"type": "thinking_delta",
					"text": " the user said \"Go away and think for a bit to plan how you'll write this\" - this seems like they want me to think about the style and approach first",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "thinking_delta",
					"text": ", then write the essay. But they're asking me to do this in the context of a coding assistant, which is",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "thinking_delta",
					"text": " a bit unusual.\n\nLet me just write the essay as requested. The user wants:\n1. Think about the style\n2. Write a",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "thinking_delta",
					"text": " 300 word essay on agentic AI context management\n\nI'll write a thoughtful, well-structured essay on this topic.",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "thinking_delta",
					"text": "",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "thinking_stop"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": "# Agentic AI Context Management",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": "\n\nAgentic AI systems—autonomous agents capable of reasoning, planning, and executing multi-step tasks—face a fundamental",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": " challenge: maintaining coherent context across extended interactions and complex workflows. Unlike simple request-response models, these agents must jug",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": "gle evolving goals, partial results, tool outputs, and user feedback simultaneously. Effective context management separates",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": " useful agents from frustrating ones.\n\n## The Core Problem\n\nContext in agentic systems isn't",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": " merely conversation history. It encompasses working memory (immediate task state), episodic memory (past interactions within a",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": " session), semantic knowledge (loaded facts and documents), and procedural memory (learned patterns and learned feedback). Managing these layers",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": " requires balancing fidelity against token economics—preserving enough context to maintain coherence while respecting context window",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": " limits and latency constraints.\n\n## Strategies for Effective Management\n\n**Hierarchical forgetting** proves essential.",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": " Agents should retain recent, high-relevance context in full detail while progressively abstracting older",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": " information into summaries or embeddings. This mirrors human cognition and enables indefinite task",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": " completion without degradation.\n\n**Semantic chunking** organizes context by meaning rather than chronology.",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": " Grouping related facts, goals, and intermediate results allows agents to retrieve relevant context efficiently without scanning entire histories",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": ".\n\n**Explicit memory management**—treating memory as a first-class concern with read/write/",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": "evict operations—beats implicit accumulation. Agents should make deliberate decisions about what to remember from each",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": " interaction and why.\n\n## Practical Considerations\n\nThe best context management strategies remain domain and task-dependent. A",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": " coding assistant needs different memory priorities than a research analyst. The key insight is that context",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": " isn't free—it has costs in compute, latency, and signal-to-noise ratio. Treating it",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": " as a resource to be managed thoughtfully, rather than accumulated indiscriminately, produces more capable and reliable agents.\n\nContext management",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
				{
					"type": "delta",
					"text": " ultimately determines whether an agent appears intelligent or merely verbose.",
					"messageId": "msg_d29a280ab001Y7oCsI0MrwXORo"
				},
